text.section:
A regulation adopted under this division that conflicts with any statute, local law, or other regulation shall govern if the regulation adopted under this division:
requires a greater width or size of yards, courts, or other open spaces;
requires a lower height of buildings;
requires a reduced number of stories;
requires a greater percentage of lot left unoccupied; or
imposes a more restrictive standard.

A statute, local law, or other regulation that conflicts with a regulation adopted under this division shall govern if the statute, local law, or other regulation:
requires a greater width or size of yards, courts, or other open spaces;
requires a lower height of buildings;
requires a reduced number of stories;
requires a greater percentage of lot left unoccupied; or
imposes a more restrictive standard.
